-- HM Revenue & Customs Chairman to Step Down, Telegraph Reports
-- B y   A n n e - S y l v a i n e   C h a s s a n y
-- 2012-04-29T10:04:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-29/hm-revenue-customs-chairman-to-step-down-telegraph-reports.html
Michael Clasper, chairman of HM
Revenue & Customs, is planning to step down amid controversy
over the U.K. tax administration’s relationship with large
companies, the Sunday Telegraph said, without citing anyone.  Clasper is expected to step down by the end of the year and
a search for a replacement has started, according to the
newspaper.  A spokesman for HMRC, who asked not to be identified in
line with departmental policy, confirmed the search is under
way, adding no date for Clasper’s departure has been announced.  A spokesman for HMRC confirmed the search and said a date for
Clasper’s departure hasn’t been set, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anne-Sylvaine Chassany in Paris at 
